CHAETAL MORPHOLOGY. Dorsal ordinary chaetae of three types : long macrochaetae (Ml), mesochaetae and microchaetae. Long macrochaetae relatively thick, slightly arc-like or straight, narrowly sheathed, feebly serrated, mostly apically rounded or rarely, mainly in lateral position, pointed (
,
). Mesochaetae similar to ventral chaetae, thin, smooth and pointed. Microchaetae similar to mesochaetae but shorter. S–chaetae of tergites thin, smooth and short, notably shorter than nearby macrochaetae (
,
).

