). Ant. IV ventrally with complete set of chaetae (3 brs, 
2 iv
; ap: 8 bs and 5 miA; ca: 2 bs and 3 miA; cm: 3 bs and 1 miA; cp: 8 miA and 1 brs).

DORSAL CHAETOTAXY AND TUBERCLES. Head with fused tubercles So and (L+1/2Dl) (

). Cephalic chaetae Dl2, Dl6 and L4 free. Th. II–III with free chaetae Di2, Di3 and De2. On Th. II–III, chaetae De3 and Dl3 absent. On Abd. I–III, line of chaetae De1–chaeta s nearly parallel to dorsomedian line. On Abd. I–III chaetae De2 free (

